org.springframework.cloud.dataflow.core.dsl

Class TransitionNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.springframework.cloud.dataflow.core.dsl.AstNode
      • org.springframework.cloud.dataflow.core.dsl.TransitionNode

  • public class TransitionNode
extends AstNode
    An AST node representing a transition found in a parsed task specification. A transition is expressed in the form "STATE->TARGET". If STATE is unquoted it is considered a reference to the exit code of the preceding app (where * means 'any exit code'). If STATE is quoted it is considered a reference to the exit status of the preceding app (where '*' means 'any exit status'). TARGET can be either a reference to a label, :foo, or a single app name Foo.
    Author:
    Andy Clement

      • getStatusToCheck

        public String getStatusToCheck()
        Return the status that should trigger the transition. For an exit code check, this will be a simple number (or *) and isExitCode will be true. For an exit status check, this will a simple string (without quotes) and isExitCode will be false.
        Returns:
        the status to check to trigger the transition

      • getStatusToCheckInDSLForm

        public String getStatusToCheckInDSLForm()
        Return the status that should trigger the transition as it would occur in the DSL. For an exit code check, this will be a simple number (or *) and isExitCode will be true. For an exit status check, this will a simple string (*with* quotes) and isExitCode will be false.
        Returns:
        the status to check to trigger the transition
